[DhtmlXQ_comment0]bk 2c 01 explained||Ok, for beginners, this is perhaps the first kill that you are mated with.||Red already has one cannon in the center. It is effectively controlling the center. Black cannot place any piece in the line of fire or it will be an immediate check.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1]This would be a checkmate as the rear cannon is performing the check.||To defend, black has to place another chess piece in the same file, but the front cannon would then be performing the check.||Therefore this is a chceckmate as black cannot resolve both checks with one move.[/DhtmlXQ_comment1]
